    "# Task 1: Problem Definition & Dataset Creation\n",
    "**Classification Problem:** Hand Gesture Recognition\n",
    "\n",
    "**Classes:** Palm, Punch, Thumb\n",
    "\n",
    "**Reason for choosing this problem :**  \n",
    "Hand gesture recognition is a practical and accessible problem with real-world applications in human-computer interaction, sign language interpretation, and touchless control systems. It is easy to self-collect using a smartphone, and the three chosen gestures are visually distinct, making it a suitable challenge for a beginner deep learning classification task.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Data Format:**  \n",
    "All images are in `.jpeg` format, captured using a smartphone camera. Images were captured at varying resolutions and later resized to 128x128 pixels during preprocessing.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Data Collection Steps:**\n",
    "1. Three gesture classes were defined: `palm` (open hand), `punch` (closed hand), and `thumb`.\n",
    "2. Photos were taken using a smartphone camera in an indoor environment.\n",
    "3. Each gesture was photographed from multiple angles (front, side, diagonal), distances (close, medium, far), and under different lighting conditions (bright and dim).\n",
    "4. Both left and right hands were used to increase variety.\n",
    "5. Images were organized into separate folders named after each class.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Best Practices Incorporated:**\n",
    "- Varied backgrounds (plain wall, floor, curtain, ceiling) to prevent the model from learning background features.\n",
    "- Varied lighting conditions to improve robustness.\n",
    "- Multiple angles and distances to capture diverse representations of each gesture.\n",
    "- Balanced classes (100 images each class) to avoid class imbalance.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Challenges:**\n",
    "- To ensure a consistent hand positioning while photographing alone was challenging.\n",
    "- Some images had motion blur due to hand movement during capture especially a picture that were taken with dim light environment.\n",
    "- Lighting inconsistency between sessions required careful selection of usable images."
   ]
