    "### Train / Split / Test \n",
    "The data undergoes spliting into three parts which is training, validation, and test sets. This is done to make sure the model does not just memorize the data but can actually perform well on new, unseen data.\n",
    "The training set, which is usually about 70% of the data, is used to teach the model. During this stage, the model learns patterns from the data.\n",
    "The validation set, around 15%, is used while the model is still learning. It helps us check how well the model is performing and allows us to adjust settings to improve it. This step is important to prevent overfitting, where the model becomes too focused on the training data and fails to generalize.\n",
    "Finally, the test set, also about 15%, is used only after the model has finished training. The model has never seen this data before, so it provides a fair evaluation of how well the model will perform in real-world situations.\n",
    "Afterall, splitting the data is  to ensures that the model is properly trained, carefully improved, and accurately evaluated."
   ]
